      "culturalSignificance": "The olive defined Athenian identity and economy for millennia. Sacred olive groves (Moriai) were protected by death penalty laws. The tree's regeneration after Persian destruction in 480 BCE became a powerful symbol of Athenian resilience. The olive branch remains the universal peace symbol (UN flag, national emblems) and 'extending an olive branch' entered common language. Olive oil maintained religious significance in later Jewish and Christian traditions (anointing kings, lamp oil in temples)."
